Each MIX has 37 LEDs, use `Pixels` command to set the right number of LEDs.

Microphone is mapped to Analog input but there is no support for sound reactive effects in Tasmota.

## Flashing

Use a prying tool or a spudger to separate back plate from the shell. 

![Use a spudger to open](/assets/device_images/lifesmart_LS168_open.webp)

Take out the PCB, the flashing pads are located left of the ESP32 module.

![Pinout](/assets/device_images/lifesmart_LS168_pinout.webp)

Connect your serial to USB adapter to TX, RX and GND. Power the controller using its USB-C port. Ground the GPIO0 (bottom hole) during powerup.